Margarites rossicus, common name : the pearly margarite, is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Margaritidae.There are two subspecies: 

Margarites rossicus derjugini Galkin, 1955 [ex Bartsch MS]
Margarites rossicus rossicus Dall, 1919Some authors place this species in the subgenus Margarites (Pupillaria)